  "prompt": "What is the best phone under 12k currently?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, here are some of the best smartphones under \u20b912,000 in India, offering great value for money based on performance, battery life, and features:\n\n### 1. **Realme Narzo 50i Prime**\n   - **Display:** 6.5-inch HD+ LCD\n   - **Processor:** Unisoc T612\n   - **RAM/Storage:** 3GB/32GB (expandable)\n   - **Camera:** 8MP rear, 5MP front\n   - **Battery:** 5000mAh\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b98,499\n   - **Highlights:** Affordable, decent battery life, and a large display.\n\n### 2. **Xiaomi Redmi 12C**\n   - **Display:** 6.71-inch HD+ IPS LCD\n   - **Processor:** MediaTek Helio G85\n   - **RAM/Storage:** 3GB/32GB (expandable)\n   - **Camera:** 50MP rear, 5MP front\n   - **Battery:** 5000mAh\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b99,999\n   - **Highlights:** Good performance, large battery, and a capable camera.\n\n### 3. **Samsung Galaxy M04**\n   - **Display:** 6.5-inch HD+ PLS LCD\n   - **Processor:** MediaTek Helio P35\n   - **RAM/Storage:** 4GB/64GB (expandable)\n   - **Camera:** 13MP dual rear, 5MP front\n   - **Battery:** 5000mAh\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b99,999\n   - **Highlights:** Reliable brand, decent battery life, and sufficient storage.\n\n### 4. **Tecno Spark Go 2023**\n   - **Display:** 6.56-inch HD+ IPS LCD\n   - **Processor:** Unisoc T606\n   - **RAM/Storage:** 3GB/64GB (expandable)\n   - **Camera:** 13MP dual rear, 8MP front\n   - **Battery:** 5000mAh\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b98,499\n   - **Highlights:** Affordable, decent performance, and good battery life.\n\n### 5. **Infinix Smart 7**\n   - **Display:** 6.6-inch HD+ IPS LCD\n   - **Processor:** MediaTek Helio A22\n   - **RAM/Storage:** 3GB/32GB (expandable)\n   - **Camera:** 13MP rear, 5MP front\n   - **Battery:** 5000mAh\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b97,999\n   - **Highlights:** Budget-friendly, large display, and good battery life.\n\n### Key Considerations:\n- **Performance:** The Xiaomi Redmi 12C and Realme Narzo 50i Prime offer the best performance in this range.\n- **Battery Life:** Most phones in this category come with a 5000mAh battery, ensuring all-day usage.\n- **Camera:** Redmi 12C and Tecno Spark Go 2023 have better camera setups.\n- **Brand Preference:** Samsung and Xiaomi are popular choices for reliability.\n\nPrices and availability may vary, so check the latest offers before purchasing.",
